##A blind man's 50 days in Wuhan

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Magpie, _ paper _ News

In the darkness, Zhang Lei suddenly heard the community radio shouting: "closed... " he was surprised, do not know what happened, do not know what means.

Blind since the age of four, Zhang Lei has lived in the dark for 32 years, and he can't remember what red and blue look like when he saw them.

He grew up alone, did not go to school, with his grandmother in the mountains, "a quiet growing up. ". Ten years ago, he came to Wuhan from his hometown of Qianjiang to study massage and work for others, saving a little money.

Until five days before the city was shut down, he paid a $50,000 transfer fee to buy a blind massage parlor in Wuchang. Shop decoration a little old, touch the wallpaper with his hand are cracked, but finally have their own place, their own master.

That day, Zhang Lei was still in the mood, looking forward to earning money, early to find a girlfriend. So when the news came that the city was closed, he was only surprised for a moment, thinking half a month at the most.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
January 23,10:00, Wuhan City bus, subway, ferry, long-distance passenger transport suspended operations, airport, railway station from the Han Channel temporarily closed. By Zheng Chaoyuan, Tang Qi, Zhou Qitu, thepaper.cn

But ten days, two weeks, a month... passed.

He spent all day in the shop, closed the door tightly, not easy to go out half-step. During the day, he washes his hands at least 10 minutes, mopps the floor three to five times with 84 disinfectant, and drinks three to five bottles of warm water; at night, he bathes every day, soaking his feet in white vinegar for more than half an hour.

Once upon a time, working for someone was a group of people living together. It was the first time he lived alone, and all sorts of concrete and trivial troubles kept popping up -- on Day 37 of lock-up, the induction cooker went "Chi Chi" and the electricity in the House went off; on Day 39 of lock-up, the shutters could not be closed, he was scared to death; on days 47 and 49, the refrigerator rumbled and the kitchen sink clogged..

He didn't have much money left. He had to pay the rent, the utilities, and the groceries every day. Food is not cheap, two cabbage, three lettuce to more than 40 pieces, there is a long time, he only vegetarian.

Luckily, volunteers were helping him, bringing him vegetables, oil, masks and alcohol. They closed the shutters, fixed the electricity, even brought him an induction cooker and a refrigerator. After the outbreak, he thought, volunteers must be given free massages.

Right now, though, he's trying to decide whether to hold on to the massage parlor. On March 7, with only a few tens of dollars left on him, he had to ask his mother for help. At one point he wanted to sell the store, but thought he should stick with it, even if he had to work to earn a little rent money.

For 50 days, he hoped the bustling city of Wuhan would soon return.

Here is his dictation

One

On January 18th, I paid a $50,000 transfer fee and took over a massage parlor.

It has more than 80 square meters, seven massage beds, four foot massage beds, a monthly rent of 5,200 yuan, in a Wuchang district inside. I was happy for a few days, finally have a massage shop of their own, want to make money after early to find a girlfriend.

I am 36 years old and have worked in the massage industry for 10 years.

Just open a few days, the store to the guests are not many, a few a day, are doing ordinary massage, 60 yuan a person. January 20, the shop to help the friends home for the New Year, I a call over, so simply closed the store, ready to open on the eighth day of the first month again. I had no idea. Three days later, the whole of Wuhan was sealed off.

That day, after I closed the massage parlor, I went to visit a friend in Hanyang. By then, there was news of pneumonia in Hankou, but we didn't think it was serious. January 23, I heard that the city of Wuhan closed, also do not mind, at that time I think at most half a month.

My friend told me to buy a mask, I said I have a mask, a disposable mask for massage wear. The other side said that this mask is useless, to buy what medical masks, said the lung disease is highly infectious. I still had my doubts. Did I say it was that bad? But I went and bought a mask.

I walked to the gate of the community, a pharmacy a pharmacy to ask, go to the third pharmacy, the clerk said there are two bags of masks, but he can only sell me a pack. I was a little surprised, but I didn't say anything, so I bought that pack. Normal surgical masks, 10 each, 10 bucks a pop, 100 bucks in total. After that, I went and bought 10 bottles of 84 disinfectant for 20 yuan.

The next day, a friend at work in Hankou told me that he had been out when he saw a man walking by the side of the road. He suddenly collapsed and never got up. When I heard that, I was so scared, I couldn't go out anymore, and I was locked in the massage parlor every day.

I don't know what to do. I don't know what to do. At first, I called the mayor's hotline, and they told me to call the Disabled People's Federation; I called the Disabled People's Federation, but no one answered; I called the community, and they told me not to go out, and occasionally helped me buy food.

I also buy food online, mobile phone installed software, hand touch what, the mobile phone will "say" what, such as text messages, Wechat have voice. A few days ago, I bought two cabbage, three lettuce, spent 40 yuan, although more expensive, but still fresh. I heard that pork belly sells for more than 50 yuan a catty, and ordinary meat costs more than 40 yuan a catty. I myself have "seen" on the Internet, more expensive, less than half a catty of meat to more than 40 yuan.

I didn't dare buy meat. I didn't have any money left. I had to pay rent and utilities every day. The evening of New Year's Eve, I bought fish balls, meatballs, spent more than 10 dollars, a person in the store boiled to eat. For a long time, I was a vegetarian, like a monk, but vegetarian dishes were also expensive.

Later I heard the news that from February 24 to March 10, Wuhan has 10 yuan 10 kinds of vegetables sold, there are potatoes, green peppers, cabbage... a total of 10 catties of vegetables. I called the neighborhood, and they said no, but I guess they got robbed. I bought the 58 yuan set meal, there are Chinese cabbage, green pepper, tomatoes... but some dishes are not fresh.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
People Buy Vegetables at a supermarket in Wuhan. By Zheng Chaoyuan, Tang Qi, Zhou Qitu, thepaper.cn

Day After Day, I don't know how long it's been, and I don't know how long it's GonNa be. I am often anxious to sleep, every night with the phone to listen to the news, massage information, martial arts novels, in a good mood can sing... usually two or three o'clock in the morning before going to bed.

A while back, I asked my landlord if I could get a month's rent off, and he didn't respond.

Two

My hometown is in Qianjiang, only an hour's drive from Wuhan.

When I was four years old, I developed measles, then a high fever, went to the hospital for Penicillin, and didn't get better. I later heard my parents say that at that time I was swollen like steamed stuffed Bun, my mother according to the rural method with a mouse tail, my eyes suddenly bulged out, very scary. Then I got a shot and my eye went back in, but I couldn't see a thing.

My parents took me to the hospital, the doctor said treatment of an eye to 50,000-60,000, but the family did not have so much money, to see a few times after giving up.

All the memories I had before I went blind, they're gone now. I've been living in the dark for as long as I can remember. When people say red, they mean red; when people say blue, they mean blue. I don't seem to have seen it, don't know what it looks like, or have forgotten what it looks like.

I grew up alone, with no friends, no school, and I grew up quiet.

My parents are both workers, there are two older sisters, but my parents work busier, older sisters have to study. I was brought up in the mountains by my grandparents. Later, they came to my home and took me shopping, to the park, to take a walk... and told me what happened to them.

My parents retired one after another, and I soon became an adult and began to want to be independent.

Blind people like us can't do anything but study massage. By contacting the Qianjiang Disabled Persons'Federation, I studied with a masseur for a year, mainly learning various massage techniques and body conditioning.

Ten years ago, I left Qianjiang and came to Wuhan on my own to study at a massage school run by the Hubei Disabled Persons'federation.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hanyang District Street, Wuhan, on the second day of the Lunar New Year on January 26. China News Service

The school has 32 students, I was not used to at first, not accustomed to communicate with strangers, but soon got along well with the students. When I left home, it was a big decision for me. In fact, parents do not agree at first, but I can not resist, I would like to see outside, also hope to learn more outside.

We learn about child massage, surgery and gynecology, as well as massage methods for breast hyperplasia in massage school. After three months there, I went to the Wuhan School for the blind for six months to study all kinds of massage.

Ever since I got out of school, I've been working for other people, eating, sleeping, two or three grand a month. Most of the time, I was in Wuhan, from one area to another area, the middle also went to Shanghai and Suzhou, but because food is not used to, did not go for long and back.

Five years ago, after I broke up with my girlfriend, I never found another girlfriend.

Every time I came home, my parents were worried, and I was worried. Working in a massage parlor doesn't pay well, and it's hard to find a girlfriend. As I got older, I decided I couldn't work for people all the time, so I decided to open my own massage parlor.

Last summer, a friend of mine told me that his boss wanted to sell the massage parlor. I have been to their store before, also with the boss, and later to "see" a few times, think this business is good, although the decoration of a little old.

On January 18th, after raising $50,000, I took over the business. At that time, there are two months to pay the rent due, leaving some rice and oil, the former boss gave me all.

I wanted to change my life, but I got stuck in a quagmire.

Three

We have a massage group with over 200 people, all blind in Wuhan. Before the closure of the city, they basically went back to their hometown, only some did not go back.

I didn't plan to go back because I had just picked up the massage parlor and my parents were pressuring me to get married. Now I regret it. You never know what you're GONNA get.

On the day of the siege, my parents called me and told me not to go out. For more than a month now, I've been alone in the massage parlor, closing the door every day.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wuhan Street, Jan. 26. China News Service

At first, I own online shopping, delivery man called to say, block the entrance of the community not to enter. I told him to tell the community, I can't see, it's not convenient to go out, let him to my door. They'd bring it in, drop it off at my door, sometimes hand it to me, and I'd open the door and wear a mask.

I'm in good health, and I never go outside, except to take out the garbage, or to get things, and I wear a mask, so I don't worry too much. But the parents are old, although the hometown is not as serious as Wuhan, I will still worry about them. I called them every day and told them not to go out, to wash their hands and drink more water.

I wash my hands at least once every 10 minutes during the day; then I mop the floor with 84 disinfectants three to five times a day; drink warm water every day, and three to five bottles of warm water in boiling bottles. Every night before going to bed, I will take a bath, with white vinegar foot half an hour, white vinegar can soften blood vessels, but also can kill bacteria.

These methods are blind school, in addition to eat less junk food, less late night, less sulking, this can also prevent new pneumonia.

In fact, I can't do it myself. I often go to bed at two or three in the morning and don't get up until ten in the morning.

February 28 at noon, I am at home cooking, induction cooker "Rush Chi" sound, may be a spark. I was scared to death, found the induction cooker burned out, the electricity in the home also trip.

I didn't know what to do, so I called the community, and the community worker said that the electrician wasn't working, and asked me to call him the next day. But I can't cook, I can't cook, I can't stay hungry. No Way, I told a friend of mine, he helped me on the Internet to send a message for help.

Soon, I received a lot of calls, Jiangsu, Gansu, Wuhan... that night at 11:00, two volunteers came, they helped me get electricity, also sent some noodles.

March 1, the shutter suddenly can not close, just contact the volunteers, they gave me a new induction cooker, a bag of rice, some vegetables, and help me close the shutter.

I'm really grateful to them, thinking about giving these volunteers free massages after the outbreak.

(the characters are pseudonyms)
